    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/458: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-17T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 17, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 17—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMGFR1">McCoy</persName> requests me to
                    advise you that he has received a letter from <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName> to the effect that the
                    Council will begin to discuss the report November 14th. This will be followed by
                    a meeting of the Committee of Nineteen and then the Special Assembly.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName> continues that
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> calculates that a
                    period of 2 months starting from the middle of November will be occupied in
                    dealing with the report and that members of the Commission should be available
                    during that period, though not necessarily continuously.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMGFR1">McCoy</persName> requests this
                    information be given the War Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
